Subinterfaces of LF in opennlp.ccg.hylo
 interface Mode
          A interface for hybrid logic nominals, to allow polymorphism for both Modality labels and variables over Modality labels.
 interface Nominal
          A interface for hybrid logic nominals, to allow polymorphism for both Nominal atoms and Nominal variables.
 

Classes in opennlp.ccg.hylo that implement LF
 class Box
          A modal box operator, such as [F]q.
 class Diamond
          A modal diamond operator, such as <P>p.
 class HyloAtom
          A logical atomic formula.
 class HyloFormula
          A parent class to implement reasonable default behavior for classes representing data structures for hybrid logic.
 class HyloVar
          A class for objects which can stand for any HyloFormula object.
 class ModalOp
          A parent class for modal operators, such as <P>p, [F]q, and <>(p ^ q).
 class ModeLabel
          A modality label.
 class ModeVar
          A class for variables over ModeLabel objects.
 class NominalAtom
          A hybrid logic nominal, an atomic formula which holds true at exactly one point in a model.
 class NominalVar
          A class for variables over NominalAtom objects.
 class Op
          A generic operator, such as conjunction, disjunction, exclusive-or, negation or optionality (^, v, v_, ~, ?).
 class Proposition
          A propositional value, such as the predicate "sleep", or the value of a semantic feature, such as "past" for tense.
 class SatOp
          A hybrid logic satifaction operator, which tests whether a formula is true a particular point named by a nominal.
